Police say the man demanded money, allowing the impression that the hairbrush in his robe pocket was a handgun. JOHANNESBURG - A man dressed in in a leopard-print robe, black mask, orange crocs, orange gloves and armed only with a hairbrush held up a Mcdonald's restaurant.The fashion-challenged criminal was arrested after a brief police chase early this morning.Police say he demanded money, allowing the impression that the hairbrush in his robe pocket was a handgun.Texas police have recovered $130 in cash from the man.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)